Akwa Ibom stakeholders on Sunday evening adopted Pastor Umo Eno, the stateâ€™s Commissioner for Lands and Water Resources as their preferred successor to Governor Udom Emmanuel in 2023, Daily Independent has gathered. Credible sources that former Governor, Obong Victor Attah, supported by the Chairman of Akwa Ibom council of Chiefs, Dr. Solomon Etuk, presented Eno as a man with the capacity to consolidate on the gains recorded by the present administration of Mr. Udom Emmanuel. Another source said the governor himself said that God revealed to him that Eno is the right man to succeed him. Several former and serving political office holders were present at the meeting. Details later.